label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 7

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the ventral lateral neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and bilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). Arbors extend further dorsally and are denser in the ipsilateral hemisphere and it descends on the contralateral side (Gorko et al., 2024). It receives input from lobula plate tangential neurons (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 8

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the ventral lateral neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and bilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). Arbors extend to the level of the esophageal foramen and are roughly symmetrical, but denser in the ipsilateral hemisphere, and it descends on the contralateral side (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron A1

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the transverse horizontal neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and contralateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024). It ascends on the contralateral side (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron A2

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the transverse horizontal neck muscle 2 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and contralateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024). It ascends on the contralateral side (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron 1

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the cervical sclerite-occipital condyle dorsoventral neck muscle 1 via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron 2

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the cervical sclerite-occipital condyle dorsoventral neck muscle 2 via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron 3

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the neck depressor muscle via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron 4

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the neck levator muscle (21) via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron 5

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the neck adductor muscle (22) via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the prothoracic neuromere (Gorko et al., 2024).

Adult doublesex-expressing neuron that has its cell body in the abdominal ganglion (Lee et al., 2002). There are over 300 of these cells in the female and close to 300 in the male (Pavlou et al., 2016). Some of these neurons innervate the internal genitalia via the abdominal nerve trunk and some ascend to the brain via the cervical connection (Rideout et al., 2010).

Adult doublesex neuron that also expresses dissatisfaction and has its soma in the posterior abdominal ganglion (Diamandi et al., 2024). Its arborization is restricted to a relatively small region of the abdominal ganglion (Diamandi et al., 2024). It is a remodeled primary neuron (Diamandi et al., 2024).

definition.value: Found in males and females by Diamandi et al. (2024), but unclear whether dimorphic.

value.value: Adult female-specific doublesex neuron that also expresses dissatisfaction and has its soma at the posterior tip of the abdominal neuromere (Diamandi et al., 2024). It is a local interneuron with broad bilateral arborization that is contained within the abdominal neuromere (Diamandi et al., 2024). It is a remodeled primary neuron (Diamandi et al., 2024). There are approximately two of these cells on each side (Diamandi et al., 2024).

Adult female-specific doublesex neuron that also expresses dissatisfaction and has its soma in the dorsal abdominal neuromere, posterior to the DDAG_D (Diamandi et al., 2024). It has broad bilateral arbors in the abdominal neuromere, crossing the midline via a ventral arch that has a medial branch giving rise to dorsal abdominal neuromere arborization, and a contralateral anterior projection into the thoracic neuromeres (Diamandi et al., 2024). It develops from the larval abdominal 6 A26g neuron, which begins to express doublesex and is remodeled during pupal development (Diamandi et al., 2024). There is one of these cells on each side (Diamandi et al., 2024).

Adult female-specific doublesex neuron that also expresses dissatisfaction and has its soma in the dorsal abdominal neuromere, anterior to the DDAG_C (Diamandi et al., 2024). It has broad bilateral arbors in the abdominal neuromere, crossing the midline via a ventral arch that has no medial branch, and a contralateral anterior projection into the thoracic neuromeres (Diamandi et al., 2024). It develops from the larval abdominal 5 A26g neuron, which begins to express doublesex and is remodeled during pupal development (Diamandi et al., 2024). There is one of these cells on each side (Diamandi et al., 2024).

Adult female-specific doublesex neuron that also expresses dissatisfaction and has its soma in the posterior abdominal neuromere (Diamandi et al., 2024). It has mainly ipsilateral arborization in the abdominal neuromere and an anterior projection that crosses the midline in the metathoracic neuromere then continues further anteriorly (Diamandi et al., 2024). It is a remodeled primary neuron (Diamandi et al., 2024).

Larval interneuron of the ventral nerve cord that is part of lineage 26 (Diamandi et al., 2024). Its soma is located dorsolaterally, close to its dorsal dendritic arbors, which extend anteriorly and posteriorly (Diamandi et al., 2024). It extends ventromedially, crossing the midline, then sharply turns back dorsally and projects anteroventrally into the thoracic neuromeres (Diamandi et al., 2024).
Any larval A26g neuron (FBbt:00053225) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of larval abdominal 4 neuromere (FBbt:00051993).
Any larval A26g neuron (FBbt:00053225) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of larval abdominal 5 neuromere (FBbt:00051994).
Any larval A26g neuron (FBbt:00053225) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of larval abdominal 6 neuromere (FBbt:00051995).
Adult doublesex neuron that has its cell body in the brain. In the central brain, there are around 70 doublesex cells per hemisphere in the female and around 140 in the male (Deutsch et al., 2024).

Doublesex neuron that is part of a cluster in the posterior medial region of the protocerebrum. There are 5 of these cells per hemisphere in the female and 60 in the male, with most derived from the DM4 neuroblast (Ren et al., 2016).

Doublesex neuron that is part of a cluster in the posterior region of the protocerebrum. There are around 26 of these cells per hemisphere in the female and around 67 in the male (Kimura et al., 2015). Some arise from the CP3 (DL2) neuroblast (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: Kimura et al. (2015) report around 27 pC1 (female) cells per hemisphere, Zhou et al. (2014) and Pavlou et al. (2016) report around 8, Ren et al. (2016) and Wang et al. (2020) report 5. Unlike in the male, there does not appear to be overlap between dsx pC1 and fru pMP-e in the female (Ren et al., 2016).

value.value: Doublesex neuron that is part of a cluster in the superior medial protocerebrum (Rideout et al., 2010). There are fewer of these cells in the female (approximately 12) than the male (approximately 16) (Robinett et al., 2010; Kimura et al., 2015).
Doublesex neuron that is found medially in the gnathal ganglion. There is up to one of these cells per hemisphere (Rideout et al., 2010; Kimura et al., 2015).

Neuropeptide F-expressing neuron of the adult that has a small cell body in the anterior dorsolateral brain (Lee et al., 2006). Its axonal projections travel into the dorsal protocerebrum (Lee et al., 2006). There are 2-3 of these cells on each side in the male and 0-1 in the female (Lee et al., 2006).

label.value: adult prothoracic ventral unpaired median neuron

value.value: Any adult VNC ventral unpaired median neuron (FBbt:00052750) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult prothoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111083).

label.value: adult metathoracic ventral unpaired median neuron

value.value: Any adult VNC ventral unpaired median neuron (FBbt:00052750) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult metathoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111085).

Adult Myoinhibitory peptide-expressing neuron with an anterior soma in the lateral protocerebrum, at the base of the medulla (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). It arborizes in the ipsilateral medulla and in the mediolateral and dorsolateral protocerebrum (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). There are three of these cells per hemisphere (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). At least one per hemisphere has wide-field tangential arborizations in a layer just distal to the lamina synaptic neuropil (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011).

definition.value: Kolodziejczyk et al. (2011) find three immunoreactive neurons, but could not determine whether all have distal lamina arbors. Not sexually dimorphic and do not produce serotonin, PDF, ITP, octopamine/tyramine or dopamine and distinct from clock neurons (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011).

label.value: adult large bilateral optic lobe serotonergic interneuron

value.value: Adult serotonergic neuron with a large cell body near the midline in the posterior protocerebrum and bilateral extensions to the optic lobes (Nassel et al., 1988; Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). In the optic lobes, it arborizes in the lobula, lobula plate and medulla synaptic neuropils (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). Its axon runs past the medulla and passes through the first optic chiasma to innervate a layer just distal to the lamina synaptic neuropil (Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Nassel et al., 1988; Kolodziejczyk et al., 2011).

definition.value: Based on descriptions, this might be a subtype of serotonergic IP neuron.

value.value: The top of the head capsule (Ferris, 1950). It bears the ocellar triangle (Ferris, 1950).
Small crescent-shaped area of thickened cuticle just dorsal to the insertion points of the antennae (Atkins, 1949).
Anterior, and smaller, of the two cervical sclerites (Fabian et al., 2016). It is fused to the posterior cervical sclerite (Fabian et al., 2016).
Posterior, and larger, of the two cervical sclerites (Fabian et al., 2016). It is fused to the anterior cervical sclerite (Fabian et al., 2016).
Anterior (medial) region of the pronotum that is mainly not visible from the dorsal perspective (Fabian et al., 2016).
Posterior branch that splits from the radius at the same point as L1 (R1) and extends distally before giving rise to L2 and L3 (Snodgrass, 1935).
Wing vein found anterior to the posterior anal vein (Fabian et al., 2016). Distally it fuses with the second anterior cubital vein (Fabian et al., 2016).
Short anteroposteriorly-oriented vein that branches from the anterior cubital vein (Stark, 1999; Fabian et al., 2016). It fuses with the first anal vein (Fabian et al., 2016).

Small vein that branches from the first anal vein and runs parallel and posterior to the anterior cubital vein (Fabian et al., 2016). It extends distally to the second anterior cubital vein (Fabian et al., 2016).
Wing vein that arises at a similar position to the median vein and runs posterior to it (Fabian et al., 2016). Distally it forks to form the first and second cubital veins (Fabian et al., 2016).
Wing vein that branches from the anterior cubital vein and follows a longitudinal course to the wing margin (Fabian et al., 2016).

label.value: fused first anal and second anterior cubital vein

value.value: Wing vein found posterior and distal to the first anal and second anterior cubital vein, beyond their fusion point (Fabian et al., 2016). It does not reach the wing margin (Fabian et al., 2016).
Break in the costal wing vein, which follows the anterior wing margin (McAlpine, 1981). These may give the wing additional flexibility during flight (McAlpine, 1981).

definition.value: McAlpine (1981) describes 3 possible breaks in insect wings, based on figures in Ferris (1950) and Fabian et al. (2016), only humeral and subcostal appear to exist in D. melanogaster.

value.value: Break in the costal wing vein just distal to the humeral crossvein (McAlpine, 1981).
Break in the costal wing vein where the subcostal vein would join if it reached the anterior wing margin (McAlpine, 1981).

label.value: second basal and discal wing cell

value.value: Entire wing cell proximal to the posterior crossvein and bounded by L4 and L5 (Lindsley and Zimm, 1992). It is comprised of the second basal and discal cells, which are not separated by a vein (Lindsley and Zimm, 1992).

definition.value: See FBrf0066905 == Lindsley and Zimm, 1992 for a good schematic identifying wing cells (intervein).

value.value: Sclerite of the medial mesothoracic postnotum (Fabian et al., 2016). On each side, it is separated from a laterotergite by the dorsoventrally-oriented postnotal ridge (Fabian et al., 2016).
Dorsoventrally-oriented apodeme that separates the mediotergite of the mesothoracic postnotum from the laterotergites (Fabian et al., 2016).

label.value: larval Ms cell of labial neuromere

value.value: Neuron of the larval labial neuromere that expresses dromyosuppressin (DMS) (Park et al., 2008). There are two of these cells per organism (Park et al., 2008).
Any larval corazonin neuron (FBbt:00052004) that has its soma located in some larval thoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111029).
Neuron that has its soma in the dorsal part of a thoracic neuromere and expresses the neuropeptide Nplp1 (Park et al., 2008).
